                                                                    <br />
                                                                    <div class="smallMarginLeftTxt">
                                                                        <h4><b>Fraud Awareness</b></h4>
                                                                         <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Because there is no foolproof way to prevent fraud, awareness is the best defence.
                                                                            Please, use your best judgment in all transactions. If you receive a suspicious
                                                                            email or are the victim of a scam, email law enforcement in your own country right
                                                                            away.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <b>Step 1:</b> If you are the victim of a scam, please email us with as much information
                                                                            about your particular situation as possible.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <b>Step 2:</b> Forward any suspicious emails to us immediately at admin@GSE-Mart.aero.
                                                                            Don't change the subject line or send it as an attachment because doing so could
                                                                            prevent us from identifying trends and preventing similar scams.)
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <b>Step 3:</b> File a complaint with the Internet Fraud Complaint Centre of your
                                                                            own country to inform the appropriate local authorities and law enforcement agencies.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            GSE-Mart.aero will investigate submitted reports in an effort to protect our customers
                                                                            against future fraud. We support law enforcement agencies in the prosecution of
                                                                            Internet criminals and work diligently to prevent fraud.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>Please be aware…</b></h4>
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            GSE-Mart.aero does not own, buy or sell GSE listed on our website. Offer GSE warehousing
                                                                            or shipping services. Get involved in transactions between buyers and sellers. Ask
                                                                            you for personal or financial information via email. Inspect vehicles listed on
                                                                            our website for fitness of purpose.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>Before you buy or sell</b></h4>
                                                                        
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            <b><i>Confirm contact information - </i></b>Always verify the buyer's location,
                                                                            address and phone number.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <b><i>Secure payment first - </i></b>Do not transfer the title until you have payment
                                                                            in hand at the agreed upon price.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <b><i>Verify that a certified payment or cheque is genuine - </i></b>Before you
                                                                            deposit a certified cheque, verify authenticity with the issuing bank-not just your
                                                                            bank. Make sure the account contains sufficient funds and the issuing bank guarantees
                                                                            payment on the check. It may take a week or more for the check to clear. It hasn't
                                                                            cleared just because your bank has accepted it and credited your account.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <b><i>Beware of overpayment or other complicated payment schemes -</i></b>Don't
                                                                            agree to any plan where the buyer asks to send a cheque for more than the sale price
                                                                            and requests that the seller refund the difference. And be suspicious of any buyer
                                                                            who proposes making payment through a friend or agent of the buyer.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>We don't own, buy or sell vehicles listed on our site.</b></h4>
                                                                        
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            GSE-Mart.aero is an online GSE listing service that connects
                                                                            GSE buyers with sellers. We are not GSE dealers. Any listing information about a
                                                                            particular piece of GSE comes directly from the seller - not
                                                                            us. If you receive an email that implies we're selling or buying a GSE resources,
                                                                            please report it to us at our email <a href="mailto:admin@GSE-Mart.aero">admin@GSE-Mart.aero</a>
                                                                            and to law enforcement agencies in your own territory. It's most certainly a scam.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>We don't offer automotive warehousing or shipping services</b></h4>
                                                                       
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Any email that requests a deposit or payment for a shipment of piece of GSE stored
                                                                            in a GSE-Mart.aero warehouse is a scam. GSE-Mart.aero doesn't own a warehouse, and
                                                                            we don't ship GSE. In simple terms, we don't get involved
                                                                            in transactions between buyers and sellers (see more below).
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            There are many reputable warehousing and shipping services that can make long-distance
                                                                            transactions easy. Just be sure to check out the services proposed on your own.
                                                                            If a seller recommends a bogus warehousing or shipping service please report the
                                                                            seller it to us via our email <a href="mailto:admin@GSE-Mart.aero">admin@GSE-Mart.aero</a>
                                                                            to us and to law enforcement in your own territory.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>We don't get involved in transactions between buyers and sellers.</b></h4>
                                                                       
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Don't respond to any email that appears to come from GSE-Mart.aero (for example,
                                                                            by displaying our logo) and urges you to complete the sale or purchase of a GSE
                                                                            listed on our site. Such emails are a sure sign of a scam.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            Other signs of fraud are emails that:
                                                                            <ul>
                                                                                <li>Claim the security of a transaction is guaranteed by GSE-Mart.aero </li>
                                                                                <li>Imply we've verified information about a particular buyer, seller or listing. </li>
                                                                                <li>Describe a "preferred" or "pre-approved" buyer or seller program. </li>
                                                                            </ul>
                                                                            GSE-Mart.aero doesn't guarantee or endorse transactions, and we don't have preferred
                                                                            or pre-approved buyers or sellers. We'll never encourage you to buy any particular
                                                                            vehicle listed on GSE-Mart.aero or to sell your GSE to any
                                                                            particular buyer. If you receive a suspicious email such as the ones described above,
                                                                            please report the seller it to us via our email <a href="mailto:admin@GSE-Mart.aero">
                                                                                admin@GSE-Mart.aero</a> to us and to law enforcement in your own territory.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>We don't ask you for personal or financial information via email.</b></h4>
                                                                       
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Online fraud often begins with a spoof email requesting financial information. These
                                                                            spoof, or scam, emails often impersonate a reputable company such as GSE-Mart.aero
                                                                            by illegally displaying a company's name, logo or trademark.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            The intent is to deceive customers into revealing information such as:
                                                                            <ul>
                                                                                <li>Username </li>
                                                                                <li>Password </li>
                                                                                <li>Bank account number </li>
                                                                                <li>Bank routing number </li>
                                                                                <li>Credit card number </li>
                                                                            </ul>
                                                                            The only time we'll ever request your credit card information is when you're in
                                                                            the process of purchasing an advert on our website. We will not take down your listing
                                                                            because you don't provide account information. If you receive an email that asks
                                                                            for the kinds of information listed above, don't respond. Instead, please report
                                                                            the seller it to us via our email <a href="mailto:admin@GSE-Mart.aero">admin@GSE-Mart.aero</a>
                                                                            to us and to law enforcement in your own territory.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>We don't inspect vehicles listed on our website for fitness of purpose or damage.</b></h4>
                                                                       
                                                                        <h4><b>GSE Inspection</b></h4>
                                                                       
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            If this is possible schedule an inspection using a professional, mechanic who is
                                                                            trained to maintain the GSE you wish to buy.
                                                                            If this is not possible ask for a full service history.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>Verify the title & Ownership</b></h4>
                                                                       
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            This can be done by requesting the appropriate paperwork and checking with previous
                                                                            owners/sellers of the GSE.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>Beware of fraudulent escrow services and protect yourself with secured payment.</b></h4>
                                                                         <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            For a fee, an escrow service holds the buyer's payment until the seller has delivered
                                                                            the item purchased. Such a third-party service can protect both parties from fraud.
                                                                            However, scammers often set up fake escrow services. They claim an affiliation with
                                                                            well-known companies like GSE-Mart.aero, to create a sense of security. GSE-Mart.aero
                                                                            does not endorse all escrow services and some well established internet banks does
                                                                            not operate an escrow service. If you wish to use Escrow services we would highly
                                                                            recommend that you use well established and reputable finance institutions.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            Remember these tips before you agree to use an escrow service:
                                                                            <ul>
                                                                                <li>Avoid any service that implies an affiliation or partnership with GSE-Mart.aero.
                                                                                </li>
                                                                                <li>Avoid any service that claims to be operated by TRUSTe. TRUSTe doesn't operate an
                                                                                    escrow service. </li>
                                                                                <li>Verify an escrow service's legitimacy by checking with state regulators. </li>
                                                                                <li>Research the escrow service </li>
                                                                                <li>Decline the transaction if the other party insists on using an escrow service that
                                                                                    you’re not sure about. </li>
                                                                                <li>Use a search engine to open the website in a different browser-don’t click on a
                                                                                    link the seller provides </li>
                                                                                <li>Dial the contact number listed </li>
                                                                                <li>Search for the company on the BBB website. </li>
                                                                            </ul>
                                                                            And once you find an escrow service you're comfortable with, be sure you understand:
                                                                            <ul>
                                                                                <li>What conditions must be met before the payment is released to the seller. </li>
                                                                                <li>What the escrow service charges. </li>
                                                                                <li>Which party is expected to pay the fee. </li>
                                                                            </ul>
                                                                            If any escrow-related email or website implies an affiliation with GSE-Mart.aero
                                                                            by displaying our logo or by other means please report the seller it to us via our
                                                                            email <a href="mailto:admin@GSE-Mart.aero">admin@GSE-Mart.aero</a> to us and to law enforcement in your own territory.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>Common-Sense Advice for Buyers</b></h4>
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Buying a car you find online is a lot like buying a car through a classified ad
                                                                            in the newspaper. In either case, use your best judgment.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Know the GSE market value</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Be suspicious of GSE priced significantly below market value. If it sounds too good
                                                                            to be true, it probably is.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Obtain GSE maintenance history or purchasing report</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Maintenance history reports can provide useful information and history about the
                                                                            GSE. You will also be able to see an audit of previous owners and who currently
                                                                            holds the title and whether the GSE has been in an accident and repaired.
                                                                            You'll also find out whether the GSE was ever reported stolen, salvaged or
                                                                            damaged.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Inspect the GSE</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            If this is possible schedule an inspection using a professional, mechanic who is
                                                                            trained to maintain the GSE you wish to buy.
                                                                            If this is not possible ask for a full service history. Keep in mind that an inspection
                                                                            isn't a warranty and won't guarantee the intended purchase is free from defects
                                                                            or that inspectors have identified all existing problems.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Confirm contact information</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Before you send payment, verify the seller's location, address and phone number
                                                                            - an email address is not enough. ZIP codes, area codes and addresses should match
                                                                            up. Be wary if the seller is located overseas and you have not done business with
                                                                            them before.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Use email wisely</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Avoid sending sensitive personal or financial information (such as your, credit
                                                                            card number or checking account number) to a seller via email. Remember that email
                                                                            communications are not secure and can be easily forwarded to others.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Get a detailed receipt</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Ask the seller for a receipt that states whether the vehicle is being sold with
                                                                            a warranty or "as is."
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Get title to the vehicle</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Make sure you know what's required in your own territory to transfer title to the
                                                                            GSE you're buying.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <h4><b>Common-Sense Advice for Sellers</b></h4>
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Selling GSE online is a lot like selling GSE through a classified
                                                                            ad in a magazine or industry newspaper. In either case, use your best judgment.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Confirm contact information</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Be particularly wary of buyers willing to purchase your GSE
                                                                            sight-unseen, especially buyers located overseas. Always verify the buyer's location,
                                                                            credentials, street address and phone number.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Secure payment first</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Do not transfer the title until you have payment in hand at the agreed upon price.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Verify that a certified check is genuine</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Before you deposit a certified check, verify authenticity with the issuing bank-not
                                                                            just your bank. Make sure the account contains sufficient funds and the issuing
                                                                            bank guarantees payment on the check. It may take a week or more for the check to
                                                                            clear. It hasn't cleared just because your bank has accepted it and credited your
                                                                            account.
                                                                        </div>
                                                                        <b>Beware of overpayment or other complicated payment schemes</b>
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <br />
                                                                        <div class="mrgLeftAndBtmTxt">
                                                                            Don't agree to any plan where the buyer asks to send a check for more than the sale
                                                                            price and requests that the seller refund the difference. And be suspicious of any
                                                                            buyer who proposes making payment through a friend or agent of the buyer.
                                                                        </div>
